In 2010, 1,704 people lived there. Highway 1 passes through the town. It is 61 km south of San Quintín and 119 km north of Cataviña. The economy is based on agriculture. Onions are the major crops here. There are many nearby fishing spots, such as Punta Baja and Isla San Jerónimo. == Other websites == * Category:Towns in Mexico Category:Settlements in Baja California (state)
